MAIN_MESSAGE: There is a power cut affecting the  SY10 postcode area of Oswestry. We had no advance warning of this and only became aware of it at  9:27pm. Our control centre will attempt to reset the network remotely to restore power in stages, and our emergency response team are on their way to the local area to investigate reports of a faulty transformer on the network. Our team will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible, and we expect the power to be restored by 11:30pm. Once they arrive, or when we receive any update regarding the cause, we will be able to provide you with more information. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 9:35pm on 21st April 2021
TRANSCRIPT: There is a power cut affecting the  SY10 postcode area of Oswestry. We had no advance warning of this and only became aware of it at  9:27pm. Our control centre will attempt to reset the network remotely to restore power in stages, and our emergency response team are on their way to the local area to investigate reports of a faulty transformer on the network. Our team will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible, and we expect the power to be restored by 11:30pm. Once they arrive, or when we receive any update regarding the cause, we will be able to provide you with more information. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 9:35pm on 21st April 2021

MAIN_MESSAGE: There is a fault with the power in the FK1 postcode area of Falkirk. This is causing flickering power to a number of properties. Our engineers have arrived on site and our team will work to get your power back to normal as quickly and as safely as possible by Midnight. We will update this message if this information changes. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 9:55 PM on Wednesday, 21 April 2021.

MAIN_MESSAGE: There is a power cut affecting the CH64 postcode area of Neston, affecting properties in The Village, The Rake and surrounding areas.  We had no advance warning of this and only became aware of it at 2:41pm. In order to complete repairs, engineers on site will need to isolate the power to other properties at 11pm and we expect the power to be restored by 3am. We will update this message if this information changes. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 10:01pm on 21st April 2021
